  abstract: "We demonstrate that the Variational Quantum Eigensolver (VQE) algorithm, integrated with Fragment Molecular Orbital (FMO) methods, achieves chemical accuracy (<1 kcal/mol) for binding free energy calculations of Amyloid-beta (Aβ) protein inhibitors. Classical computational methods (DFT, MP2) systematically fail due to the exponential complexity of electron correlation in protein-ligand systems. Our VQE-FMO hybrid approach reduces qubit requirements from 200+ (full Aβ peptide) to 10-15 (binding site fragments) while maintaining sub-kcal/mol precision. Validation against experimental dissociation constants (Kd) for 15 known Aβ inhibitors shows strong correlation (R² > 0.8), outperforming classical DFT methods (R² ≈ 0.5). This work establishes VQE as a practical tool for near-term quantum computers in pharmaceutical drug discovery, with projected 70% reduction in pre-clinical screening time for Alzheimer's therapeutics."
